<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Absor on Server Populations and Economies</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=408203" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top">
		    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    Absor replied to some comments regarding server population and the economy:
<blockquote>
<p>
3) Yes, there is a growing population at the higher levels on mature servers. Similar to the point about item decay, the only way to prevent this 'problem' would be to have levels 'decay' by some means. That's also not really going to be popular with players…</p>
<p>
We've added content for the growing population at those levels. And that helps a lot.</p>
<p>
But if you start a new character on even the oldest of servers, you will notice that the newbie zones are not empty. The influx of new players has been steady. Players that have played for a while will start new characters. People will try playing on a different server to see what the atmosphere is like there. The newbie zones aren't empty at all.</p>
<p>
Alan</p>

<p>[<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000048.html">Read more on the Developer's Corner</a>]</p>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=408203">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
			  </td>
		</tr>

		</table>

	</td>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
</table>



